g to Moscow to discuss future procurement.\n\nII. ASIA-AFRICA\nLibya asks for new round of negotiations on US air base and aid.\nIndonesian dissidents continue as disruptive force.\n\nIII. THE WEST\nLatest French plans for nuclear testing.\nDe Gaulle believed ready to press for Algerian settlement despite army opposition.\nCypriot negotiators seen ready to accept indefinite postponement of independence rather than agree to present British demands.\n\nDominican Republic--Widespread arrests believed to have forestalled anti-regime plotting.\nVenezuela--Demonstrations may take place on today's anniversary of Perez Jimenez' overthrow", "token_count": 97, "token_end_0based": 96, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "23 january 1960 i the communist bloc uar general going to moscow to discuss future procurement ii asia-africa libya asks for new round of negotiations on us air base and aid indonesian dissidents continue as disruptive force iii the west latest french plans for nuclear testing de gaulle believed ready to press for algerian settlement despite army opposition cypriot negotiators seen ready to accept indefinite postponement of independence rather than agree to present british demands dominican republic widespread arrests believed to have forestalled anti-regime plotting venezuela demonstrations may take place on today's anniversary of perez jimenez overthrow", "unred_source_page": 3}
